node.title: Hundreds of people told to isolate after Omicron exposure at Melbourne bars
node.alt: A woman wearing protective gear stands next to a car
node.description: Health officials confirmÂ a person with the Omicron variant attended venues in Fitzroy and Collingwood on Friday night, potentially exposing hundreds of people to the virus.
node.content:
["Hundreds of people have been told to isolate after a person with the Omicron COVID-19 variant attended two busy\u00a0Melbourne bars\u00a0on Friday night.", "Victoria's health department said the positive case attended Sircuit Bar in Fitzroy, between 9pm and midnight on December 10, and then the Peel Hotel in Collingwood until 3am.", "It's estimated around 320 people were at the Peel Hotel\u00a0and 410 people were at Sircuit Bar during those exposure times.", "The health department said anyone who attended the venues must get tested and quarantine immediately.", "Fully vaccinated people must quarantine for seven days, and people who are not fully vaccinated must quarantine for 14 days.", "The health department yesterday confirmed three new cases of the Omicron variant, bringing\u00a0the total number of confirmed cases in the state to six.", "Two of the new Omicron cases were\u00a0on a flight from Dubai from which previous cases were identified.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
